Sustainable production of “synthetic” natural gas (SNG) is possible through the conversion of CO2 and water (H2O) into CH4 and oxygen (O2) using renewable energy such as sunlight. This reaction proceeds as follows:1CO2+2H2O→CH4+2O2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
